Atrium (at) rather short (n = 10). Penis (p) long and stout. Epiphallus (e) long, about two times as long as penis; flagellum (fl) longer than epiphallus and terminated in folded coil. Appendix very small, extends from folded coil of flagellum, about same length as epiphallus. Penial retractor muscle (pr) short, thickened and inserted distally on penis. Vas deferens (vd) narrow tube connecting epiphallus and free oviduct (
Fig. 6A
).

Internal penial wall corrugated into series of thick penial pilasters (pp), which form a fringe around penial verge. Penial verge (pv) rather long and curved, conical, with smooth surface and orifice located at tip (
Fig. 6B
).

Vagina cylindrical, about two times as long as penis. Gametolytic duct very long, proximal to genital orifice large, coiled; distal to genital orifice tapering to small tube, short, about one-third length of proximal part and connected to enlarged gametolytic sac. Oviduct and albumin gland small (
Fig. 6A
).

Internally, vaginal wall performs longitudinal vaginal pilasters (vp); proximal to genital orifice with small corrugated continuous ridges, ridges distally becoming smooth (
Fig. 6B
).
